1
00:00:14,438 --> 00:00:16,667
(Episode 12)

2
00:00:22,908 --> 00:00:25,318
(Lee Joo Hun confesses the truth behind Jeong Se Yeon's death)

3
00:00:40,458 --> 00:00:41,498
Soo Ho.

4
00:00:52,007 --> 00:00:53,308
It's you again.

5
00:00:54,477 --> 00:00:55,608
Yes.

6
00:01:03,248 --> 00:01:04,418
It's me again.

7
00:01:05,888 --> 00:01:07,418
I wanted to see you,

8
00:01:11,427 --> 00:01:12,597
and here you are.

9
00:01:15,398 --> 00:01:17,168
I came to give you a hug.

10
00:02:40,347 --> 00:02:42,347
Do you feel better?

11
00:02:43,947 --> 00:02:46,287
I don't have a lot of memories with my dad.

12
00:02:47,257 --> 00:02:48,727
After my mom passed away,

13
00:02:49,958 --> 00:02:51,828
he was mostly in the States.

14
00:02:53,898 --> 00:02:55,828
I lived with my grandmother,

15
00:02:57,197 --> 00:02:59,137
and I started living alone once I entered middle school.

16
00:03:01,697 --> 00:03:03,238
It must've been tough.

17
00:03:05,877 --> 00:03:07,477
I hated him for a long time.

18
00:03:10,007 --> 00:03:13,218
I had a lot of pent up anger toward him,

19
00:03:14,947 --> 00:03:16,447
and I finally let it out.

20
00:03:18,387 --> 00:03:20,257
I thought that would make me feel better.

21
00:03:21,718 --> 00:03:23,058
But I still feel uneasy.

22
00:03:38,738 --> 00:03:40,778
I don't know if it's because I still can't forgive him...

23
00:03:42,148 --> 00:03:43,678
or if it's because I feel bad for him now.

24
00:03:45,548 --> 00:03:47,078
I'm still not sure...

25
00:03:50,588 --> 00:03:52,018
what it is that I'm feeling right now.

26
00:04:10,968 --> 00:04:13,977
What? You just ran out in the middle of your lesson?

27
00:04:13,977 --> 00:04:15,708
Honey, calm down. Just talk it out with her.

28
00:04:15,847 --> 00:04:17,507
Where is your mind at?

29
00:04:17,907 --> 00:04:21,218
Don't you know that this is an important period for you?

30
00:04:22,688 --> 00:04:24,148
How dare you?

31
00:04:24,747 --> 00:04:26,018
Don't you dare glare at me like that!

32
00:04:28,888 --> 00:04:31,557
- That little... - Honey, wait.

33
00:04:31,758 --> 00:04:34,758
Honey, please. Calm down.

34
00:04:38,898 --> 00:04:41,237
What do you think you're doing? Open the door right now!

35
00:04:41,237 --> 00:04:44,008
Honey, I'll talk to her, so please stop.

36
00:04:44,008 --> 00:04:45,208
Open the door!

37
00:05:12,297 --> 00:05:14,838
Mr. Kang, how are things at the office?

38
00:05:15,037 --> 00:05:16,167
It's a complete mess.

39
00:05:16,708 --> 00:05:19,737
The reporters and Black Soul fans are in front of the building.

40
00:05:19,907 --> 00:05:21,537
And it's caused serious damage to the agency.

41
00:05:21,938 --> 00:05:23,708
Your father probably has a lot on his mind too.

42
00:05:41,628 --> 00:05:48,737
("Missing You")

43
00:06:29,578 --> 00:06:31,847
(Dear Soo Ho and Seo Jun)

44
00:06:31,847 --> 00:06:34,078
(I wasn't going to write this because it felt so corny.)

45
00:06:34,078 --> 00:06:35,117
Hey.

46
00:06:35,117 --> 00:06:36,847
(Congratulations on winning first place, Se Yeon!)

47
00:06:37,347 --> 00:06:38,388
Here.

48
00:06:39,617 --> 00:06:42,188
Gosh, it's loose.

49
00:06:43,927 --> 00:06:46,727
- You're wearing the hat crooked. - Wear this.

50
00:06:52,997 --> 00:06:54,797
Dear Soo Ho and Seo Jun.

51
00:06:54,797 --> 00:06:56,268
- How do I look? - It looks nice on you.

52
00:06:56,737 --> 00:06:59,037
I wasn't going to write this because it felt so corny.

53
00:07:00,737 --> 00:07:02,547
I wasn't able to thank you guys when I won the first place...

54
00:07:02,547 --> 00:07:04,347
because I was busy crying.

55
00:07:04,347 --> 00:07:05,747
(Congratulations on winning first place, Se Yeon!)

56
00:07:06,378 --> 00:07:07,718
I'm writing a letter hoping you guys won't feel upset.

57
00:07:13,157 --> 00:07:15,357
I always had a lonely life,

58
00:07:16,188 --> 00:07:17,458
but thanks to you guys,

59
00:07:19,057 --> 00:07:21,057
the past three years of my life were filled with warmth.

60
00:07:22,698 --> 00:07:25,938
Thanks to our time together, I was able to laugh a lot,

61
00:07:27,367 --> 00:07:28,737
gain more confidence,

62
00:07:30,867 --> 00:07:32,537
and finally achieve my dream.

63
00:07:43,388 --> 00:07:45,188
Today's the best day of my entire life.

64
00:07:47,157 --> 00:07:49,057
And I will always remember...

65
00:07:50,458 --> 00:07:51,787
you guys were with me today.

66
00:07:56,667 --> 00:07:58,128
My precious friends.

67
00:08:00,097 --> 00:08:01,297
I love you guys.

68
00:08:03,968 --> 00:08:07,307
I know I'll feel embarrassed if you guys read this letter,

69
00:08:08,438 --> 00:08:10,278
so I hope you never find it.

70
00:08:11,778 --> 00:08:12,948
From Se Yeon.

71
00:08:32,667 --> 00:08:34,568
Do you know what Se Yeon said the day we bought this?

72
00:08:35,838 --> 00:08:37,107
He hoped that our friendship would last forever.

73
00:08:37,107 --> 00:08:38,737
I told him to stop being so childish.

74
00:08:41,078 --> 00:08:42,208
Yes, you did.

75
00:08:43,208 --> 00:08:45,048
Back then, I took it for granted.

76
00:08:46,347 --> 00:08:48,418
So I thought we'd always be together forever.

77
00:08:50,718 --> 00:08:53,357
But who knew he'd die so quickly?

78
00:08:55,088 --> 00:08:56,227
I know.

79
00:08:57,257 --> 00:08:58,487
It really didn't last long.

80
00:08:59,428 --> 00:09:01,298
I wasn't there for him when he was having a hard time.

81
00:09:02,298 --> 00:09:04,468
And I regret it so much.

82
00:09:05,938 --> 00:09:07,397
But he's no longer around.

83
00:09:09,068 --> 00:09:11,637
So I ended up taking it out on you...

84
00:09:13,477 --> 00:09:14,977
because it made me feel better.

85
00:09:17,777 --> 00:09:19,277
I was so caught up with how hurt I was...

86
00:09:20,218 --> 00:09:21,617
that I didn't know that you were hurting inside as well.

87
00:09:25,218 --> 00:09:26,357
I'm sorry.

88
00:09:33,097 --> 00:09:34,397
What's the matter with us?

89
00:09:44,767 --> 00:09:47,178
(Missed call, Dad)

90
00:09:51,948 --> 00:09:53,678
How's your dad handling this?

91
00:09:54,218 --> 00:09:55,347
I don't know.

92
00:09:57,017 --> 00:09:59,487
In the past, I was so jealous of you for having a rich dad.

93
00:10:00,058 --> 00:10:01,458
But now I'm not jealous at all.

94
00:10:02,257 --> 00:10:03,387
Why were you jealous?

95
00:10:03,788 --> 00:10:05,027
You have a mom.

96
00:10:05,588 --> 00:10:06,857
Are you trying to compete with who has a sadder life?

97
00:10:07,828 --> 00:10:09,668
Your family's rich.

98
00:10:10,497 --> 00:10:11,928
I'm not sure that's true anymore.

99
00:10:11,997 --> 00:10:13,538
Rich people don't have problems eating three meals a day...

100
00:10:13,668 --> 00:10:15,568
even if they go bankrupt.

101
00:10:15,568 --> 00:10:16,708
You mean they're okay for three generations.

102
00:10:17,168 --> 00:10:18,938
- You idiot. - What?

103
00:10:18,938 --> 00:10:20,977
You really know nothing.

104
00:10:20,977 --> 00:10:23,948
Gosh, who threw this cigarette bud?

105
00:10:25,507 --> 00:10:27,647
Are you talking to me?

106
00:10:32,017 --> 00:10:34,188
Did you just throw this cigarette bud at us?

107
00:10:34,188 --> 00:10:35,828
What kind of a gangster are you?

108
00:10:35,828 --> 00:10:37,857
Look at this kid. He just called us gangsters.

109
00:10:37,857 --> 00:10:39,198
- Who is this kid? - Who?

110
00:10:39,698 --> 00:10:41,928
- Look at those kids. - Who are you boys?

111
00:10:42,227 --> 00:10:43,298
What's your problem?

112
00:10:44,468 --> 00:10:45,767
What's your deal?

113
00:10:45,767 --> 00:10:47,737
Hey, kid. Come over here.

114
00:10:48,468 --> 00:10:49,668
Look at him.

115
00:10:50,607 --> 00:10:51,708
Just hold your anger.

116
00:10:51,968 --> 00:10:54,007
Hey. Run.

117
00:10:54,538 --> 00:10:55,607
Hey.

118
00:10:56,007 --> 00:10:57,948
- Hey... Hey. - Catch them.

119
00:10:58,078 --> 00:10:59,277
- Come over here. - Hey!

120
00:10:59,277 --> 00:11:02,347
- Hey! Get over here! - Where do you think you're going?

121
00:11:02,818 --> 00:11:04,448
- Catch them. - Are you going to throw that?

122
00:11:06,218 --> 00:11:07,418
What do you think you're doing?

123
00:11:08,418 --> 00:11:09,527
Catch them!

124
00:11:09,527 --> 00:11:10,987
- Go! - Get over here!

125
00:11:11,257 --> 00:11:12,897
- Hey! - Come here!

126
00:11:12,897 --> 00:11:14,397
- Get over here! - Go get them!

127
00:11:14,627 --> 00:11:16,968
- Hey, come here! - Run!

128
00:11:18,027 --> 00:11:19,168
Catch them!

129
00:11:19,168 --> 00:11:21,097
- Get back here! - Go get them!

130
00:11:22,867 --> 00:11:23,908
Catch them!

131
00:11:28,237 --> 00:11:29,377
- Run! - Catch them!

132
00:11:29,448 --> 00:11:31,877
- Run faster! - Go get them!

133
00:11:32,408 --> 00:11:33,918
Hey!

134
00:11:35,218 --> 00:11:36,247
My gosh.

135
00:11:39,487 --> 00:11:41,188
- My gosh. - Darn it.

136
00:11:41,188 --> 00:11:42,857
My gosh, what's this smell?

137
00:11:43,527 --> 00:11:45,527
- Darn it. - Come out here.

138
00:11:45,958 --> 00:11:48,328
- What's this smell? - They jumped into a pile of feces.

139
00:11:48,757 --> 00:11:50,328
What did they use to fertilize this place?

140
00:11:50,328 --> 00:11:52,298
Consider yourselves lucky.

141
00:11:52,867 --> 00:11:54,468
- Let's go. - Okay, boss.

142
00:11:54,767 --> 00:11:57,538
- My gosh. - Seriously.

143
00:11:59,808 --> 00:12:00,877
You and your temper!

144
00:12:00,877 --> 00:12:02,178
I didn't know!

145
00:12:03,747 --> 00:12:05,048
Hey. I carried you.

146
00:12:05,918 --> 00:12:06,918
My arm hurts.

147
00:12:07,647 --> 00:12:08,647
It stinks.

148
00:12:10,418 --> 00:12:11,548
Get off of me.

149
00:12:23,227 --> 00:12:25,267
Ju Kyung should see you now.

150
00:12:26,267 --> 00:12:27,568
Because she'd be disappointed?

151
00:12:28,468 --> 00:12:30,107
Do you think that would make her go to you?

152
00:12:30,708 --> 00:12:33,637
I never said that. Do I make you nervous?

153
00:12:33,737 --> 00:12:34,808
Obviously.

154
00:12:35,178 --> 00:12:36,308
Are you over her yet or not?

155
00:12:36,607 --> 00:12:37,808
It's not that easy.

156
00:12:38,708 --> 00:12:41,078
Then what? Do you plan to tell your feelings for her?

157
00:12:41,448 --> 00:12:43,487
Are you stupid? She's going out with you.

158
00:12:43,987 --> 00:12:45,147
Get over it.

159
00:12:45,788 --> 00:12:48,458
- It's not that easy. - Then what do you plan to do?

160
00:12:48,718 --> 00:12:50,828
I don't know. Get away from me.

161
00:12:50,828 --> 00:12:52,928
- Don't touch me. - I didn't.

162
00:12:53,357 --> 00:12:56,568
You have poop all over your face. You reek.

163
00:12:56,568 --> 00:12:57,767
Look who's talking.

164
00:13:02,568 --> 00:13:04,637
(Period Makeup)

165
00:13:08,408 --> 00:13:09,578
Are you finally registering?

166
00:13:09,708 --> 00:13:11,908
Yes. I got paid today.

167
00:13:12,107 --> 00:13:14,347
Will you be the next Selena?

168
00:13:14,347 --> 00:13:16,418
(Will you be the next Selena?)

169
00:13:47,678 --> 00:13:48,918
Hello.

170
00:13:49,117 --> 00:13:50,487
I came to register.

171
00:13:50,487 --> 00:13:52,387
Okay. Please fill this out.

172
00:13:55,718 --> 00:13:59,027
(Name: Lim Ju Kyung)

173
00:14:10,968 --> 00:14:12,568
Stop spilling.

174
00:14:17,007 --> 00:14:18,178
- Should I add rice? - Yes.

175
00:14:28,357 --> 00:14:31,127
Thanks. Get me some water.

176
00:14:39,698 --> 00:14:40,968
It's mine.

177
00:14:41,968 --> 00:14:43,168
Don't show off that you're dating.

178
00:14:48,208 --> 00:14:49,237
Did you two make up?

179
00:14:50,507 --> 00:14:51,877
I said to stay out of it.

180
00:14:51,977 --> 00:14:53,117
How can I?

181
00:14:53,247 --> 00:14:55,847
Didn't you fight because of the rumor that she and I are dating?

182
00:14:56,188 --> 00:14:57,288
You petty loser.

183
00:14:58,617 --> 00:15:01,517
There must be a reason why she can't tell the others...

184
00:15:01,987 --> 00:15:03,188
that you two are dating.

185
00:15:03,227 --> 00:15:04,357
Like what?

186
00:15:06,757 --> 00:15:08,798
I think it's because of Soo Jin.

187
00:15:09,497 --> 00:15:10,497
Soo Jin?

188
00:15:11,997 --> 00:15:15,038
How are you in a relationship when you're this dense?

189
00:15:16,668 --> 00:15:19,137
You've been on my mind these days.

190
00:15:21,377 --> 00:15:22,777
(Girlfriend)

191
00:15:37,857 --> 00:15:38,887
Hi...

192
00:15:40,527 --> 00:15:43,298
Don't laugh. How did it go today?

193
00:15:43,568 --> 00:15:44,968
It almost went well.

194
00:15:45,127 --> 00:15:47,137
The ending was quite the spectacle.

195
00:15:47,897 --> 00:15:49,568
Why? What happened?

196
00:15:49,568 --> 00:15:50,968
We rolled on a field of poop.

197
00:15:52,068 --> 00:15:53,838
I didn't know you could make jokes.

198
00:15:54,007 --> 00:15:56,678
How's your leg? Wasn't it tiring walking with a crutch?

199
00:15:57,347 --> 00:15:58,808
You should take it easy.

200
00:15:58,908 --> 00:16:02,418
I read that bananas, spinach, safflower, broccoli, and oranges...

201
00:16:02,418 --> 00:16:03,617
are good for healing broken bones.

202
00:16:03,617 --> 00:16:05,387
Remember that.

203
00:16:05,387 --> 00:16:07,257
Bananas, spinach, safflower...

204
00:16:09,257 --> 00:16:10,288
Why are you laughing?

205
00:16:10,357 --> 00:16:12,857
I like hearing you nag. Keep going.

206
00:16:14,298 --> 00:16:15,527
Stop that.

207
00:16:16,428 --> 00:16:18,828
That's right. I have something for you.

208
00:16:19,468 --> 00:16:20,497
What is it?

209
00:16:21,038 --> 00:16:22,068
Hold on.

210
00:16:22,767 --> 00:16:23,838
Where is it?

211
00:16:24,137 --> 00:16:25,208
Ta-da!

212
00:16:26,377 --> 00:16:27,637
Don't you have anything for me?

213
00:16:29,847 --> 00:16:30,877
Me?

214
00:16:35,578 --> 00:16:36,647
Ta-da!

215
00:16:38,887 --> 00:16:40,017
Here's another one.

216
00:16:42,718 --> 00:16:45,688
- Ju Kyung! - I said to knock.

217
00:16:45,788 --> 00:16:47,658
- Take this. - What?

218
00:16:52,397 --> 00:16:53,438
Gross.

219
00:16:53,468 --> 00:16:56,908
I'm going to kill you! I'll kill you!

220
00:17:01,408 --> 00:17:02,408
Hey.

221
00:17:03,808 --> 00:17:05,277
Good night. I'll call you tomorrow.

222
00:17:11,418 --> 00:17:12,517
Gross!

223
00:17:29,868 --> 00:17:33,507
What's this? Hey, Seo Jun. Open this door.

224
00:17:33,777 --> 00:17:35,378
Hey! Hey!

225
00:17:35,708 --> 00:17:36,777
Seo Jun!

226
00:17:47,418 --> 00:17:49,928
I finally get to see you. See you at school.

227
00:17:51,527 --> 00:17:55,257
Come home early, will you? You're just like your dad.

228
00:17:55,257 --> 00:17:57,598
- See you later. - That brat.

229
00:18:02,537 --> 00:18:04,438
- I'm here. - Already?

230
00:18:14,848 --> 00:18:16,317
You must've left home early.

231
00:18:16,688 --> 00:18:18,648
You should've gone straight to school.

232
00:18:18,648 --> 00:18:20,257
We have to hide it at school though.

233
00:18:20,517 --> 00:18:22,087
Let's walk like this to the bus stop.

234
00:18:23,587 --> 00:18:27,227
Are you okay with it? You wanted to tell the others.

235
00:18:27,598 --> 00:18:30,468
I was blinded by jealousy, that was why.

236
00:18:31,398 --> 00:18:32,468
Jealousy?

237
00:18:33,267 --> 00:18:34,968
Why were you jealous?

238
00:18:35,668 --> 00:18:37,868
Let's tell them once you're comfortable with it.

239
00:18:40,408 --> 00:18:42,837
- Did Soo Jin... - What?

240
00:18:44,908 --> 00:18:46,108
Never mind.

241
00:18:48,448 --> 00:18:49,517
Hey.

242
00:18:51,388 --> 00:18:52,648
Your zipper was open.

243
00:18:53,757 --> 00:18:54,918
Thanks.

244
00:18:55,118 --> 00:18:57,928
You transferred, right? I saw you in the teachers' office.

245
00:18:58,287 --> 00:18:59,658
Yes.

246
00:19:02,128 --> 00:19:03,468
Joo Hye Min.

247
00:19:04,668 --> 00:19:05,698
What a pretty name.

248
00:19:14,037 --> 00:19:16,007
Ju Kyung. Lim Ju Kyung!

249
00:19:44,277 --> 00:19:45,847
Lim Ju Kyung?

250
00:19:52,186 --> 00:19:53,287
Let's go, Soo Jin.

251
00:20:06,027 --> 00:20:07,366
Why is Hye Min here?

252
00:20:08,497 --> 00:20:10,106
That was our uniform.

253
00:20:10,507 --> 00:20:12,366
Did she transfer here? Why?

254
00:20:12,767 --> 00:20:14,537
What's wrong? Do you feel sick?

255
00:20:14,777 --> 00:20:18,406
What? No, I'm fine.

256
00:20:21,777 --> 00:20:24,146
Soo Ho! Is your dad retiring?

257
00:20:24,146 --> 00:20:26,716
What's up, my friend? Congratulations on your recovery.

258
00:20:27,017 --> 00:20:28,616
Applause. Applause.

259
00:20:29,456 --> 00:20:30,727
Congratulations for what?

260
00:20:34,827 --> 00:20:35,926
Soo Ho.

261
00:20:36,866 --> 00:20:38,626
Did you lose the cast?

262
00:20:38,866 --> 00:20:40,797
- What about it? - I did.

263
00:20:41,497 --> 00:20:42,497
Are they going to fight?

264
00:20:42,866 --> 00:20:43,936
Good.

265
00:20:46,406 --> 00:20:47,436
Are you sleeping already?

266
00:20:48,906 --> 00:20:51,277
- Yes. - What's with this lukewarm mood?

267
00:20:51,406 --> 00:20:52,547
It's good, but...

268
00:20:52,547 --> 00:20:54,876
You should get along with your friends.

269
00:20:55,277 --> 00:20:58,317
Ju Kyung! You're here. Check this out.

270
00:20:58,517 --> 00:21:01,087
I entered you in the Newstagram Queen Contest...

271
00:21:01,087 --> 00:21:03,327
and you're in second place.

